o decide what values, morals, beliefs, characteristics, ethics, schemata's are worthy to be past down to the next generation? &#10;Reading through your comments, most seem to stem from fear. Fear that someone might not do as good a job as you would like them too. Fear that those of a lower social strata may not have the resources you would like them to posses. Fear that someone might raise a child who has a view point different from your own. &#10;Try pushing your narrow world view a side for a minute and think outside the square.&#10;You might find the world goes round quite well without your approval."/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="897" language="en" documentId="1191" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Roadslesstravelled" date="31 July 2010 3:52pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6921481" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="1" thumbsDown="0" origId="1191" notes="" title="Home education: precious, not dangerous"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="45"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="46" end="285"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="286" end="425"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="426" end="742"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="743" end="827"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="828" end="897"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59"/></xmi:XMI>